    "comment": "Rationale: Snapin facilitates the synchronization of synaptic vesicle fusion. Snapin null mutant mice show reduced frequency of miniature excitatory postsynaptic currents (mini-EPSCs) and smaller release-ready vesicle pool (RRP) size (Fig.1), snapin deficiency results in EPSCs with multiple peaks and increased rise and decay times, reflecting \"desynchronized\" SV fusion (Fig.3).. Experimental description: M&M : \"Snapin (+/-) breeders were backcrossed with C57/BL6 wild-type **mice** every 3-4 months to maintain well-defined genetic background while minimizing genetic drifts.\"",
